aes::semantic(relation_permission_name_collision)

  × `read` is defined as both a relation and a permission
   ╭─[test.aes:4:7]
 3 │ type user {
 4 │   let read = dummy;
   ·       ──┬─
   ·         ╰── previously defined as a relation here
 5 │   def read = dummy;
   ·       ──┬─
   ·         ╰── defined as a permission here
 6 │ }
   ╰────
  help: `let` defines stored relations, `def` defines computed permissions — they cannot share the name `read`
